        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 7:35PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 735 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wenona, or 13 miles southwest of Streator, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rutland and Wenona.
</description>
        <instruction>Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. If outdoors,
consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
